ðŸ“„ Cisco_ISE_REPRESENTATIVE.md

# Cisco ISE Configuration (Representative Excerpt)

This configuration is a representative, non-production excerpt intended to demonstrate
Cisco ISE policy design, segmentation logic, and quarantine workflows.

## Security Group Tags (SGTs)

SGT 10  GUEST  
SGT 20  CONTRACTOR  
SGT 30  EMPLOYEE  
SGT 40  ADMIN  
SGT 99  QUARANTINE  

## Authorization Profiles

PERMIT_STANDARD_ACCESS  
Access-Type: ACCESS_ACCEPT  
SGT: EMPLOYEE  
VLAN: 30  

ADMIN_PRIVILEGED_ACCESS  
Access-Type: ACCESS_ACCEPT  
SGT: ADMIN  
VLAN: 40  

QUARANTINE_ACCESS  
Access-Type: ACCESS_ACCEPT  
SGT: QUARANTINE  
VLAN: 99  
Redirect-URL: https://ise-portal.example/quarantine  

## TrustSec Matrix

EMPLOYEE â†’ EMPLOYEE : ALLOW  
EMPLOYEE â†’ ADMIN : DENY  
EMPLOYEE â†’ QUARANTINE : DENY  
ADMIN â†’ ALL : ALLOW  
QUARANTINE â†’ ANY : DENY  

## Authorization Policy Logic

IF Device_Trust_State == "Compromised"  
THEN Apply QUARANTINE_ACCESS  

IF User_Group == "Admin"  
THEN Apply ADMIN_PRIVILEGED_ACCESS  

ELSE Apply PERMIT_STANDARD_ACCESS  

## Compliance Mapping

AC-3  
AC-6  
AU-2  
IR-4  
SC-7





