# CSfC Network Operations Portfolio

This public repository contains **sanitized, representative samples** of a CSfC-aligned Network Operations & Engineering Support Platform.

## Scope
- CSfC / NIAP / DISA STIG-aligned network operations
- Tier 2 / Tier 3 incident response and outage handling
- PKI operations (issuance, validation, revocation, compromise handling)
- Infrastructure as Code (Terraform / AWS CDK)
- Compliance automation, auditing, and evidence readiness

## What This Repository Is
- A **portfolio** demonstrating operational maturity, security engineering judgment, and compliance awareness
- A **safe-to-share** subset of a larger private platform

## What This Repository Is Not
- A production deployment
- A complete implementation
- A source of real credentials, IPs, or operational details

## Key Capabilities Demonstrated
- Secure device baselines (Cisco IOS-XE, ASA)
- Centralized logging and AAA integration
- PKI failure and compromise response
- Major outage response and communications discipline
- Audit scoring, verification matrices, and RCA methodology

# SECURITY NOTE â€“ REDACTION & DISCLOSURE PHILOSOPHY

This repository intentionally excludes or sanitizes all sensitive operational data.

## Removed or Redacted
- Real IP addresses, subnets, hostnames, domains
- VPN peers, tunnel-groups, trustpoints
- Certificates, serial numbers, private keys
- Usernames, password hashes, SNMP strings
- TACACS / RADIUS shared secrets
- Internal runbook contacts and escalation lists
- Internal ticketing or monitoring URLs

## Redaction Strategy
- All sensitive fields replaced with `REPLACE_ME_*`
- Only structural, policy, and control logic retained
- Configurations limited to representative excerpts

## Rationale
This approach balances:
- Demonstrating real-world CSfC operational competence
- Protecting security, customers, and prior environments
- Maintaining ethical and professional disclosure standards

